      "full_name": "Joint Stock Company Tula Machine Building Plant",
      "is_primary": true
    }
  ],
  "remarks": "JSC Tula Machine Building Plant is a Russian defence manufacturer with a specialisation in the production of advanced military equipment, particularly in the domain of anti-aircraft weaponry and artillery systems. The company is responsible for the development and manufacturing of several key defence systems, including the KASHTAN anti-aircraft missile and artillery system, the PALMA anti-aircraft artillery system, and a range of 30 mm automatic cannons and machine guns such as the Gryazev-Shipunov GSh-6-30 and the 2A72. These systems are integrated into various military platforms, including infantry fighting vehicles such as the BMP-3 and BTR-80A, and are also mounted on strategic assets such as the Kuznetsov class aircraft carrier.",
  "@context": "https://www.ammitto.org/ontology/context.jsonld"
}